This paper is about preparing Korean data for parsing morphologically rich languages, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heuristics and labeling rules, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of automatic morphological analysis, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or neural networks (cs.NE).
